==English==

===Etymology===
Borowed in the late nineteenth century from {{etyl|no|en}} {{term|Marita|lang=no}}. By [[folk etymology]] explained as a Spanish diminutive of [[Maria]], in analogy with [[Anita]].

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# {{given name|female|from=Ancient Greek}} occasionally used in English.

===Anagrams===
* [[amrita#English|amrita]], [[Amrita#English|Amrita]]
* [[tamari#English|tamari]]

